The volume of the cone is $\frac{1}{3} \pi r^2 H,$ and the volume of the prism is $\pi r^2 h.$  The height of the cone is $H = h - r,$ so the ratio of the volume of the cone to the volume of the prism is
\[\frac{\frac{1}{3} \pi r^2 (h - r)}{\pi r^2 h} = \boxed{\frac{h - r}{3h}}.\]

Let the cone have radius $r$ and height $h,$ and let the prism have height $h$ and base $BCDE$ as shown below.

